ship between deaf and hearing people, and offers compelling illustrations of the intertwined, and sometimes knotted, nature of individual and collective identities within Deaf culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / People with Disabilities.2bisacsh  aBrenda.  aBrueggeman.  abeyond.  adeaf.  aexploration.  aexplore.  agoes.  aidentity.  aitself.  ameans.  anature.  anotion.  apolitics.  aprobing.  asimple.  athis.  avery.  awhat.40uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814791271.001.0001zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814791271zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814791271/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA